<br>
The fix requires 1 array of 60 floating point constants, and a dozen lines in two functions, the one that adds xp to someone, and the one that removes xp upon death.<br>
<br>
They can dig up the old changes to hybrid xp, and the lines to fix hell levels would be exactly just after these.<br>
<br>
It's not a technical problem, it's a design decision.<br>
<br>
Heck, they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> KNEW</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> why there were hell levels when Kunark got out. People had been dissecting the math for ages. Yet, they deliberately chose the make every post 50 level a hell level, and make double hells.<br>
