<br>
Here is what a Hell Level really is.  <br>
Simple description:  Hell Levels, which are 30, 35, 40, and 45, require double the amount of exp a normal level would to get through it due to a mathmatical bug Verant made when increasing the difficulty curve of levels.<br>
<br>
Detailed Description:<br>
Ok, we know it's a math bug..  the exp difficulty curve is raised at levels 30, 35, 40 and 45.  Verant made an error in their math calculations, so that when the curve is increased.. you have to &quot;catch up to&quot; where the system thinks your exp should be at..<br>
Example..  (Numbers are purely made up for this example..)<br>
<br>
Level 29 will take 100,000 exp points to get through it..<br>
Level 30 will take 210,000 exp points to get through it..<br>
Level 31 will take 110,000 exp points to get through it..<br>
<br>
So you see that Level 30 -should- be 105,000 exp...  but since there is a bug there, you have to gain double the exp that would normally be needed..<br>
<br>
ALSO, levels 31, 36, 41 and 46 are bugged in that when you die, you LOSE double the normal death exp..  Normal deaths are 10 percent (2.5 blues, or half a yellow) exp loss.. Post-Hell levels are 20 percent exp loss..<br>
<br>
Yekim Forbeis<br>
50 Barbarian Rogue<br>
<br>
Soluth Soulvoid<br>
51 DarkElf Necromancer<br>
<br>
The Rathe<br>
