<br>
When SKs/Rangers/Paladins and Bards all lost their Hybrid penalty, no "extra" xp was ever awarded.  Nobody woke up levels higher than before.<br>
<br>
In fact, the raw amount of xp earned for a kill remained unchanged.  The only difference, was that AFTER xp was awarded to the hybrid, a modifier was applied to that amount.<br>
<br>
Simplistically it would read thus:<br>
<br>
XP split -> Class "checked" and modifier applied -> XP added to hybrid.<br>
<br>
This was done on a class basis (easy to tell if you are a hybrid I presume).<br>
<br>
I could envision VI trying to apply modifiers in the same fashion on a level basis.  Meaning basically the only way to benefit from the new modifier is to currently BE the level that is being modified.<br>
<br>
I surmise that doing the class modifier is easier, as it will exist for the life of the character.  Level based mods would affect ALL classes, and even then only portions of the time.  The hang up would be doing the "check" that for a class doesn't really happen.<br>
<br>
At least that's how I would approach it.<br>
<br>
At any rate, there is precedence for lessening xping burdens, and when it happened there was no "reimbursement" of any kind.  Not that there wasn't much b*tching about it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/14/02 2:16:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10258.topic&index=99>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible link to hell level removal?</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;There are no mathematical errors. The same making up of experience for 30, 35, 40 etc is the same making up of experience you see at 51, 52, 53, etc. Its the exact same thing. <br>
<br>
True, but there is a difference.<br>
<br>
30-45 was an unexpected result of how they implemented xp.  51-60 was a deliberate use of this result to cause these levels to take more xp.<br>
<br>
So 30-45 are a bug.  51-60 are by design.  Important distinction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usawin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sawin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/14/02 2:24:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10258.topic&index=100>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible link to hell level removal?</span><hr size=1> Gnome Paladins and SKs , 1/2ling Rangers Abd Paladins , Cats And Dogs Living together , Has The whole World Gone Mad ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=10258.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=10258.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=10258.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=10258.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a> <b>5</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=10258.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=10258.topic&start=121&stop=136>7</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showPrevMessage?topicID=10258.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showNextMessage?topicID=10258.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><b